{"id":37221,"date":"2019-05-05T17:47:24","date_gmt":"2019-05-05T07:47:24","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/?p=37221"},"modified":"2022-05-26T09:04:59","modified_gmt":"2022-05-25T23:04:59","slug":"skilled-occupation-lists","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-occupation-lists\/","title":{"rendered":"Multiple Occupation Lists Explained"},"content":{"rendered":"[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text]From March 2018 there are multiple occupations lists for the different visa programs.<\/p>\n<p>These occupation lists are set out in <strong>5 different legislative instruments<\/strong>. This means that every legislative instrument contains its own MLTSSL, STSOL or ROL lists.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>MLTSSL<\/strong> stands for Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List<\/li>\n<li><strong>STSOL<\/strong> stands for Short-term Skilled Occupation List<\/li>\n<li><strong>ROL<\/strong> stands for Regional Occupation List<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>These lists replaced the old SOL (Skilled Occupation List) and CSOL (Consolidated Skilled Occupation List).<\/p>\n<p>Looking at this in detail:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Legislative instrument <a href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/Details\/F2022C00574\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>LIN 19\/051<\/strong><\/a> contains the MLTSSL, STSOL and ROL lists for the Subclass <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-independent-189-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>189<\/strong><\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-nominated-190-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>190<\/strong><\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-work-regional-491-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>491<\/strong><\/a>\u00a0and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-graduate-485-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>485<\/strong><\/a> visa programs.<\/li>\n<li>Legislative instrument <a href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/Details\/F2020C01118\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>LIN 19<\/strong><strong>\/048<\/strong><\/a> contains the MLTSSL, STSOL and ROL lists for the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/temporary-skill-shortage-tss-482-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Subclass 482 (TSS)<\/strong><\/a> visa program.<\/li>\n<li>Legislative instrument <a href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/Details\/F2021C00335\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>LIN 19\/049<\/strong><\/a> contains the MLTSSL list for the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/employer-nomination-186-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Subclass 186<\/strong><\/a> visa program.<\/li>\n<li>Legislative instrument <a href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/Details\/F2020C01125\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>LIN 19<\/strong><strong>\/047<\/strong><\/a>\u00a0contains the MLTSSL and ROL lists for the <a href=\"https:\/\/immi.homeaffairs.gov.au\/visas\/getting-a-visa\/visa-listing\/regional-sponsor-migration-scheme-187\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Subclass 187<\/strong><\/a> visa program.<\/li>\n<li>Legislative instrument <a href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/Details\/F2019L00277\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>LIN 19\/050<\/strong><\/a>\u00a0contains the MLTSSL, STSOL and ROL lists for the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/training-407-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Subclass 407<\/strong><\/a> visa program.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>In summary, from March 2018 there are <strong>5 MLTSSL lists, 3 STSOL lists <\/strong>and <strong>4 ROL lists<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>It is key that applicants check which is the relevant list according to the visa program they wish to apply for.[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;20&#8243;][nectar_global_section id=&#8221;109315&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#822